					<h2 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">What Is Human Resource Management?</h2>				</div>
				</div>
		<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-06ef5fb e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child" data-id="06ef5fb" data-element_type="container">
				<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-1ed6391 elementor-widget__width-initial elementor-widget elementor-widget-theme-post-excerpt" data-id="1ed6391" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="theme-post-excerpt.default">
				<div class="elementor-widget-container">
					Human Resource Management (HRM) is more than just a department that handles payroll and recruitment, HRM is the strategic core of any organization. Whether you’re a small start‑up or a large corporation, understanding what HRM is and why it matters can help you build a strong workforce and a sustainable business. In this article we unpack the definition of HRM, explain its roles and explore why it’s indispensable to organizational success. By the end, you’ll know how HRM functions can support your business and how ANVI can be your partner in building a people‑first culture.				</div>
